									<h5>Lachen Astro-Tour Itinerary</h5>
        <h5>Late Afternoon:</h5>
        <p>Arrive in Lachen, a serene village nestled in the Himalayas, during the late afternoon. Check into your accommodation and freshen up for the evening ahead.</p>
        
        <h5>Early Evening:</h5>
        <p>Meet with your local guide or astronomy expert who will lead the astro tour. Enjoy a warm and hearty dinner at a local eatery to energize yourself for the night's activities.</p>
        
        <h5>Evening:</h5>
        <p>Depart from Lachen in the early evening, heading to a designated stargazing spot away from the village lights. Lachen offers numerous secluded areas with minimal light pollution, providing excellent visibility of the night sky.</p>
        <p>Set up telescopes and other stargazing equipment under the guidance of your expert. Learn about the constellations, stars, and other celestial objects visible in the dark Himalayan skies.</p>
        <p>Spend time observing and photographing celestial wonders such as the Milky Way, planets, and distant galaxies.</p>
        
        <h5>Late Night:</h5>
        <p>Continue stargazing and astrophotography until late into the night, taking advantage of the clear and unpolluted skies of Lachen. Engage in discussions with your guide and fellow participants, exchanging knowledge and experiences related to astronomy and the cosmos.</p>
        
        <h5>Early Morning:</h5>
        <p>As the night comes to an end, pack up your equipment and prepare for the journey back to Lachen. If time permits and weather conditions allow, witness the breathtaking sight of the sunrise over the snow-capped peaks of the Himalayas.</p>
        
        <h5>Morning:</h5>
        <p>Arrive back in Lachen in the early morning hours, feeling inspired and rejuvenated by your astro-tour experience. Take some time to reflect on the mesmerizing beauty of the night sky and the wonders of the universe before continuing your exploration of Lachen and its surrounding areas.</p>
    

									
